-- Australia Takes Three Quick Wickets After Making 311 in 2nd Test
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2012-04-16T22:29:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/australia-takes-three-quick-wickets-after-making-311-in-2nd-test.html
Australia ’s bowlers took three
quick wickets late on day two of the second cricket Test against
West Indies after scoring 311 in its first innings.  Mike Hussey top scored for Australia with 73, sharing an
89-run stand for the seventh wicket with  James Pattinson  that
was twice interrupted by rain in Port of Spain, Trinidad. Kemar
Roach took three second-day wickets to record figures of 5-105.  Australia fast bowler Ben Hilfenhaus, spinner Michael Beer
and Pattinson then removed the West Indies’ top three batsmen
leg-before-wicket as the home team stuttered to 49-3 at stumps
to trail by 262 runs.  Australia won the first Test in Barbados by three
wickets. The final match in Dominica starts April 23.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  